content: Hello dear students, long time no see!
Today, you will hopefully be very active and hardworking,
so we can make lots of nice discoveries together.
But to make us warm, lets heat up the fingers first.

Today, I will discuss with you a variant, which is rather interesting for me.
The i11 opening is known as black  advantage,
but its far from black win.
Therefore, lots of analysis is required in such opening.
But recently, many players use this 5th move.
in Tallinn Open, in last month, I played this variant with Andry as white.
andry as white or you as white
but his future titles are still ahead
according to the strict rank rules in Estonia, 4d is very good rank.
in my opinion, estonian 4d is about same as russian 6-7 d
why has different dan rule in each country
because dan system is decided by each country
national federation decides the rank system
japanese ranks are quite strict too, i think.
but in russia and china and korea, too easy to get high dan
lets continue discussion of the game.
which one is better for white in your opinion?
tough to say, h7 looks safer
Andry does not like to play against 8-h10, according to Ants' words,
but he forgot about it when he put this 5th move,
10 - stops the point of three black lines
11, stops the point of three white lines
We played till here quite fast.
but for example Tunnet is the big fan of this move.
If you are as white against him, you can be sure he will put this 13.
What is the idea of this move?
gain territory at the upper left area
keep tempo,get bigger space,wait some fouls of white
every 13 here should be a space move
so the question is which of the space moves to choose
I think it is rather psychological purpose :D
but it doesnt have to be space move.
because sometimes new moves may have good element of surprise and pressure for opponent,
something different against well known moves
even if it is not very strong move
so it doesnt have to be a space move
this 13 gives mroe possible attack lines
So, we need to understand the difference here
I have seen so many different 14th moves here.
Since it is "out of theory" 13, nobody knows exactly where is best 14
much time for white to choose 14th
there are two main logics here:
hoping it would go to normal itself
but this hope is not good, because black may choose another 15 here
so white has to be ready for that
then try to avoid being moved back to common theory
many other ideas may be possible
but these two are easiest to think.
i think this 14 is very good
However, I remember having lost one fast game (15 minute tournament) in our club, as white here,
and after that I didnt analyse it much.
Today we can take a look at it.
To see if it is possible or not
